Boot MS Server DVD
Select Repair your computer
Choose option "Troubleshoot"
Advanced Options > Command Prompt

   d:
   cd windows\system32
   ren Utilman.exe Utilman.exe.old
   copy cmd.exe Utilman.exe

Close Command prompt > Continue

on boot/logon screen hit WindowsKey+U

now set the password via
   net user administrator <password>


to clean up do the reverse
  ren Utilman.exe Utilman.exe.new
  cp Utilman.exe.old Utilman.exe


http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc748993.aspx#BKMK_cmd

http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=39273

